race.comment: RADIANT LIGHT (1) comes into this off an 85-day break and without a trial which is somewhat of a niggle. Though his form last campaign makes for good reading, finishing behind King Of Light (Belgravia yesterday) two back and jumping favourite in a Saturday race after that. Looks to have plenty of talent and can put it all together today. AUSSIE REACTOR (4) flew home from a mile back first-up in a stronger race at Ascot and looks set for a successful campaign. The wide draw is a niggle again, but he has stacks of improvement up his sleeve and he's sure to be finishing strongly once again. DOMINATUS (3) is another that rattled home last start at Ascot in a CL1. He was $17 there but held his own in tougher company. Pike rides now and if he can take closer order from the draw, he'll go close. TRAILER TRUCK (6) can build on a nice debut performance here 10 days ago. SHOW ON THE ROAD (5) gets the blinkers on and is not to be discounted off a good debut.
